===Etymology===
From [[w:Latin|Latin]] Chrīstus, from [[w:Ancient Greek|Ancient Greek]] Χριστός, noun use of χριστός, ''khristos'' meaning ''[[anointed]]''. The word Christian is first used in Antioch, according to Acts xi.25-26.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}


# {{context|Christianity}} follower of the [[Jesus Christ]] described in the Bible.
# {{context|Christianity}} one who is Born again as described in the book John chapter 3.
# {{context|Christianity}} one who is saved as described in the book of Ephesians chapter 2 and the book of Romans chapter 10 verse 9

